Strategy Design pattern:

Problem:-
When the children of a parent class have a different implementation of a parent method, but in that children some have the same implementation of that specific method, code duplication happens

Why this pattern exists:
To remove the code duplication in these kind of scenarios we use Strategy design pattern 

Real world example:
Vehicle -> drive method 
offroad, sports, goods - children of the vehicle
offroad, sports - need one kind of implementation of drive method
goods - needs one kind of implementation of drive method 

To solve this we use this pattern:
We create a drive strategy class, which has different ways of implementing the drive function, then use that inside the implementation of the vehicle class 

Class diagram:


Implementation:

```java
interface DriveStrategy {
    void drive();
}

class OffRoadDriveStrategy implements DriveStrategy {
    public void drive() {
        System.out.println("Driving off-road");
    }
}

class SportsDriveStrategy implements DriveStrategy {
    public void drive() {
        System.out.println("Driving fast");
    }
}

class GoodsDriveStrategy implements DriveStrategy {
    public void drive() {
        System.out.println("Driving carefully with goods");
    }
}

class Vehicle {
    private DriveStrategy driveStrategy;

    public Vehicle(DriveStrategy driveStrategy) {
        this.driveStrategy = driveStrategy;
    }

    public void setDriveStrategy(DriveStrategy driveStrategy) {
        this.driveStrategy = driveStrategy;
    }

    public void drive() {
        driveStrategy.drive();
    }
}

class OffRoadVehicle extends Vehicle {
    public OffRoadVehicle() {
        super(new OffRoadDriveStrategy());
    }
}

class SportsVehicle extends Vehicle {
    public SportsVehicle() {
        super(new SportsDriveStrategy());
    }
}

class GoodsVehicle extends Vehicle {
    public GoodsVehicle() {
        super(new GoodsDriveStrategy());
    }
}
```

How it works:
- The vehicle does not decide how to drive itself.
- Instead, it gets a strategy object that knows how to drive.
- This avoids duplicate code and makes behavior easy to change.

Example usage:

```java
Vehicle offRoad = new OffRoadVehicle();
offRoad.drive();

Vehicle sports = new SportsVehicle();
sports.drive();
```

